race.comment: PENROD (5) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a nose from the winner in second over 1000m at Townsville after being in the firing line on the corner. Has his share of talent and will prove hard to beat in this suitable race. MOOCHI STARLIGHT (2) pushed forward from a wide draw last time out and found the front, holding the lead for most of the way and sticking on well to finish second over 1200m at Rockhampton. Solid run last time and will take catching again. SHEMAKESMENERVOUS (12) has been in great form with two placings in succession, most recently when beaten 3 lengths into third over 1200m at Rockhampton. Nicely placed to give this a mighty shake. MISS MOLLY ROCKET (8) finished 2.25 lengths from the winner in seventh over 1000m at Gosford last start after being in the firing line on the turn, a less impressive effort than her fourth on debut at Port Macquarie the run before. Beautifully placed and is sure to take a ton of beating.
